Provides a configuration for the cron system.

@author Gunnar Wrobel <p@rdus.de>
@version 1.0
@package service_cron

@module os_gentoo     The os_gentoo module is required for Gentoo support.

@fact operatingsystem Allows to choose the correct actions depending
                      on the operating system

@param global_editor      Sets the default editor for cron.
                          (Default: '/usr/bin/emacs')
@param sysadmin           Reports are being sent to this person.
                          (Default: 'root@localhost')
@param run_services       Determines if the cron service should be started.
                          (Default: true)
@param system_continuous  Is this a continuously running machine? Machines that
                          are often turned off need a different cron mode.
                          (Default: true)
